    <section id="research">
        <h2>Research Projects</h2>
        <h3>1. Independent Research</h3>
        <h4>The Superposition Principle and the Riemann Hypothesis</h4>
        <p>
            Introduces <em>G(s)</em>, leveraging wave interference to connect primes and non-trivial zeros of the zeta function. 
            Explores fractal-like structures for insights into proving the Riemann Hypothesis.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Publication:</strong> Under review in <em>Ramanujan Journal</em>. <a href="https://zenodo.org/records/14165028" target="_blank">Zenodo</a>.
        </p>

        <h4>Modular Forms in Combinatorial Optimization</h4>
        <p>
            Develops modular forms-based algorithms for the Asymmetric Traveling Salesman Problem (ATSP), bridging number theory and combinatorial optimization.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Publication:</strong> <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.15546" target="_blank">ArXiv</a>.
        </p>

        <h3>2. Ph.D. Research</h3>
        <h4>Topological Data Analysis, AI-Driven Predictive Modeling, and Optimization of Agrivoltaic Systems</h4>
        <p>
            Highlights include:
            <ul>
                <li>Mathematical modeling of plant dynamics under spatiotemporal shading.</li>
                <li>Hybrid AI models for predicting crop yield based on geometric shadow patterns.</li>
                <li>Economic optimization using iso-profit curves to improve agrivoltaic profitability.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </section>

